## A.2 Graph Taxonomy

```
TYPE 1: CHUNK GRAPHS
  - One per chunk during prompt normalization
  - Persistent/archived — historical evidence for AMT
  - Contains: keywords, topics, entities, grammar rels, modality detections
  - Enables smart reconstruction at any token limit via span positions

TYPE 2: FILE GRAPHS
  - One per attached file — output of the file's modality pipeline
  - Created during Phase 1 (normalization), before modality graph creation
  - Used as input for: supplementary classification, modality graph construction
  - Classified as primary/supplementary AFTER creation (not before)

TYPE 3: MODALITY GRAPHS
  - One per modality — primary knowledge representation
  - Created Phase 2 (before AMT)
  - Lifecycle: Created → SemanticEnriched → CrossLinked → Stable → Updated

TYPE 4: AMT TREE
  - Built Phase 3 from chunk + modality graph evidence
  - Drives blueprint creation
```

## A.3 Smart Chunking System

```
SMART CHUNKING — Enables cross-model token-limit reconstruction

Original Prompt (full text)
  └── Chunk Graph (per chunk)
        ├── prompt_start_char / prompt_end_char  ← absolute positions
        ├── sentence_boundaries: [SentenceBoundary]
        ├── paragraph_breaks: [usize]
        ├── keyword_nodes, grammar_rels, modality_detections
        └── cleaned_text (after overlap resolution)

RECONSTRUCTION AT ANY TOKEN LIMIT:
  Given: target_token_limit, model_id
  1. Query chunk graphs for relevant span ranges
  2. Use sentence_starts/ends to find clean boundaries at target limit
  3. Reconstruct clean text from original prompt positions
  4. Works for any model: GPT-4 (128k), Claude (200k), local 7B (4k)
```

