## B.1 Universal Semantic Edge Types

Add to EVERY modality's edge enum:

```rust
// === SEMANTIC INFERENCE (grammar/action-verb derived) ===
Performs,           // subject performs action on object
Affects,            // X affects Y (causal influence)
Implies,            // X implies Y (logical entailment)
Contradicts,        // X contradicts Y
Elaborates,         // X elaborates on Y
Summarizes,         // X summarizes Y
Supports,           // X supports claim Y
TemporalPrecedes,   // X happens before Y in time
TemporalFollows,    // X happens after Y in time
CausedBy,           // X was caused by Y
Enables,            // X enables Y to occur
Prevents,           // X prevents Y from occurring
PartOf,             // X is a part of Y (structural membership)
HasPart,            // Y has part X (inverse of PartOf)
FunctionalRole,     // X serves a functional role in Y
InstanceOf,         // X is an instance of type Y
HasInstance,        // Y has instance X (inverse of InstanceOf)
SimilarTo,          // X is similar to Y (structural/semantic similarity)
RelatesTo,          // Generic relationship (fallback for unclassified)

// === VERSIONING / DERIVATION ===
DerivedFrom,        // X was derived from Y (hierarchical origin)
VersionOf,          // X is a version of Y
RefinesTo,          // X refines / improves Y
ForkedFrom,         // X was forked from Y

// === CROSS-MODALITY ===
ReferencesModality, // text node references modality content
ReferencedBy,       // modality node referenced by text (inverse)
DescribedBy,        // X described by Y (usually text)
Describes,          // X describes Y (inverse)
ImplementedIn,      // X implemented in Y (concept → code)
Implements,         // X implements Y (inverse)
VisualizedAs,       // X visualized as Y (image/3D)
Visualizes,         // X visualizes Y (inverse)
SyncedTo,           // Temporal sync (audio ↔ video)
SyncedBy,           // Reverse sync
```

**Note on edge types vs EdgeProvenance:** These are RELATIONSHIP TYPES between nodes. EdgeProvenance (Section B.4) answers a different question: what source object produced this edge itself.

