## B.4 EdgeProvenance — Source-Object Based (Granular Form)

EdgeProvenance answers: **"What object was this edge derived from?"** — not the method. The granular indexed form enables full traceability.

```rust
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize, Default)]
pub enum EdgeProvenance {
    #[default] Unknown,

    // SOURCE OBJECT TYPES
    DerivedFromPrompt,                  // from original prompt text
    DerivedFromChunk(u32),              // from chunk at index N
    DerivedFromChunkGraph(u64),         // from chunk graph ID N
    DerivedFromModalityGraph(u64),      // from another modality graph ID
    DerivedFromFile(String),            // from attached file (path/name)
    DerivedFromFileGraph(u64),          // from a file graph ID
    DerivedFromAMT,                     // from AMT tree analysis
    DerivedFromAMTBranch,               // from a specific AMT branch
    DerivedFromBlueprint(u32),          // from blueprint step N
    DerivedFromBlueprintStep(u32),      // alias for clarity
    DerivedFromMethodology(u64),        // from methodology application
    DerivedFromCrossModal,              // from cross-modality analysis pass
    DerivedFromHook,                    // from ZSEI semantic hook

    // VERSIONING ORIGINS
    VersionOf(u32),                     // this is version N of original edge
    ForkedFrom(u64),                    // forked from edge ID N
}
```

