## B.6 Universal ZSEI Hook Implementation

Every modality must fully implement all four hooks. No stubs.

```rust
// HOOK 1: OnGraphCreated
// Responsibilities:
//   1. Create ZSEI container for this graph
//   2. Register in bootstrap root container for this modality
//   3. Build materialized_path for each node: "/[ModalityName]/[NodeType]/[NodeId]"
//   4. Index all node keywords in ZSEI keyword index
//   5. Record graph creation in GraphState with provenance
//   6. Register in CrossModalIndex if cross-modal refs already present

// HOOK 2: OnInferRelationships
// Responsibilities:
//   1. LLM zero-shot: discover semantic rels not captured structurally
//   2. Parse → add new edges with provenance=DerivedFromHook
//   3. Add new inferred concept nodes where relationships require them
//   4. DO NOT add confidence — validate through consecutive loop

// HOOK 3: OnEdgeCompletion
// Responsibilities:
//   1. Verify both endpoints exist (error if not)
//   2. Set is_cross_modal flag for cross-modal edges
//   3. Update hotness_score on connected nodes
//   4. Check for duplicate edges, merge if identical type+provenance source
//   5. Update cross_modal_refs on affected nodes

// HOOK 4: OnCrossModalityLink
// Responsibilities:
//   1. Register in CrossModalIndex (Section B.7)
//   2. Set cross_modal_index_id on the edge
//   3. Update materialized_path on both endpoints
//   4. Notify target modality graph's hook processor
//   5. Store reverse edge in target graph with DerivedFromCrossModal provenance
//   6. Update GraphState.cross_modal_edge_count on both graphs
//   7. Add CrossModalRef to both nodes' cross_modal_refs vec
