## B.7 Cross-Modal Index (NEW — from Z.ai, extended)

A dedicated indexed structure for efficient cross-modal lookup. Stored in ZSEI as a project-level container.

```rust
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize, Default)]
pub struct CrossModalIndex {
    pub index_id: u64,
    pub project_id: u64,
    pub workspace_id: u64,

    // === ENTRIES ===
    pub entries: Vec<CrossModalEntry>,

    // === LOOKUP INDICES (rebuilt from entries, not persisted) ===
    #[serde(skip)]
    pub by_source_graph: HashMap<u64, Vec<u64>>,    // graph_id → entry_ids
    #[serde(skip)]
    pub by_target_graph: HashMap<u64, Vec<u64>>,
    #[serde(skip)]
    pub by_relationship: HashMap<String, Vec<u64>>, // edge_type → entry_ids
    #[serde(skip)]
    pub by_modality_pair: HashMap<(String, String), Vec<u64>>, // (src_mod, tgt_mod) → entry_ids

    // === VERSIONING ===
    pub version: u32,
    pub last_updated: String,
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize)]
pub struct CrossModalEntry {
    pub entry_id: u64,
    pub source_graph_id: u64,
    pub source_node_id: u64,
    pub source_modality: String,
    pub target_graph_id: u64,
    pub target_node_id: u64,
    pub target_modality: String,
    pub relationship: String,       // edge type name
    pub weight: f32,
    pub bidirectional: bool,
    pub provenance: EdgeProvenance,
    pub created_by_step: Option<u32>,
    pub created_at: String,
}

impl CrossModalIndex {
    pub fn rebuild_indices(&mut self) {
        self.by_source_graph.clear();
        self.by_target_graph.clear();
        self.by_relationship.clear();
        self.by_modality_pair.clear();

        for entry in &self.entries {
            self.by_source_graph.entry(entry.source_graph_id).or_default().push(entry.entry_id);
            self.by_target_graph.entry(entry.target_graph_id).or_default().push(entry.entry_id);
            self.by_relationship.entry(entry.relationship.clone()).or_default().push(entry.entry_id);
            self.by_modality_pair
                .entry((entry.source_modality.clone(), entry.target_modality.clone()))
                .or_default()
                .push(entry.entry_id);
        }
    }

    pub fn links_for_node(&self, graph_id: u64, node_id: u64) -> Vec<&CrossModalEntry> {
        let source_ids = self.by_source_graph.get(&graph_id).map(|v| v.as_slice()).unwrap_or(&[]);
        let target_ids = self.by_target_graph.get(&graph_id).map(|v| v.as_slice()).unwrap_or(&[]);
        self.entries.iter()
            .filter(|e| {
                (source_ids.contains(&e.entry_id) && e.source_node_id == node_id) ||
                (target_ids.contains(&e.entry_id) && e.target_node_id == node_id)
            })
            .collect()
    }
}
```

## B.8 ModalityEngine Trait (from Z.ai)

All engine pipelines must implement this trait for polymorphic dispatch.

```rust
pub trait ModalityEngine: Send + Sync {
    fn modality_id(&self) -> u64;
    fn modality_name(&self) -> &str;

    // === CORE (required) ===
    fn create_graph(&self, analysis: serde_json::Value, project_id: u64) -> Result<u64, String>;
    fn query_graph(&self, graph_id: u64, query: serde_json::Value) -> Result<serde_json::Value, String>;
    fn get_graph(&self, graph_id: u64) -> Result<serde_json::Value, String>;
    fn update_graph(&self, graph_id: u64, updates: serde_json::Value) -> Result<(), String>;

    // === SPATIAL (optional) ===
    fn supports_spatial(&self) -> bool { false }
    fn spatial_query(&self, _graph_id: u64, _query: serde_json::Value) -> Result<serde_json::Value, String> {
        Err("Spatial queries not supported by this engine".into())
    }

