# SECTION Q: BLUEPRINT / METHODOLOGY / PIPELINE GUIDELINES

## Q.1 Blueprint

A Blueprint is an ordered sequence of steps derived from the AMT. Always created fresh — never search-first.

```rust
pub struct Blueprint {
    pub blueprint_id: u64,
    pub task_id: u64,
    pub project_id: u64,
    pub workspace_id: u64,
    pub steps: Vec<BlueprintStep>,
    pub intent_summary: String,
    pub methodology_ids: Vec<u64>,
    pub modality_graph_ids: Vec<u64>,
    pub total_tokens_used: u32,
    pub total_duration_secs: f32,
    pub steps_completed: u32,
    pub steps_failed: u32,
    pub graph_updates_triggered: u32,
    pub amt_expansions_triggered: u32,
    pub version: u32,
    pub version_notes: Vec<VersionNote>,
    pub created_at: String,
    pub completed_at: Option<String>,
    pub state: BlueprintState,
}

pub enum BlueprintState { Created, Executing, Paused, Completed, Failed, PartiallyComplete }

pub struct BlueprintStep {
    pub step_index: u32,
    pub intent_description: String,
    pub pipeline_id: u64,
    pub pipeline_name: String,
    pub action: String,
    pub parameters: serde_json::Value,
    pub reads_from_graphs: Vec<String>,
    pub writes_to_graphs: Vec<String>,
    pub depends_on_steps: Vec<u32>,
    pub applicable_methodology_ids: Vec<u64>,
    pub initial_state: StepStatus,
    pub stages: Vec<String>,
}
```

## Q.2 Methodology Format Rules

```
NAME: Short, domain-specific (e.g. "Scientific Data Integrity")
CATEGORY: Scientific | Engineering | Mathematical | Biological | Linguistic |
          Architectural | Safety | Performance | Quality | Security | Other
APPLICABLE_MODALITIES: [] = all, ["code"] = code only
PRINCIPLES: max 10, ordered by priority (1=highest), each actionable
HEURISTICS: condition → action pairs, concrete not philosophical
DECISION_RULES: named conditional logic with specific criteria
```

## Q.3 Pipeline Format Rules

```
1. NAMING: PascalCase types, snake_case folders, sequential IDs never reused
2. INPUT: serde #[serde(tag = "action")] enum
3. OUTPUT: always success: bool + error: Option<String>
4. HEADLESS: binary callable with --input '<json>' → stdout JSON
5. ZSEI: OZONE_ZSEI_PATH env var, never hardcode paths
6. REQUIRED ACTIONS for modality pipelines:
   Analyze, CreateGraph, UpdateGraph, QueryGraph, GetGraph, TriggerSemanticHook
7. OPTIONAL: Export, StreamToUI, RunSimulation/Analysis
8. MAIN: parse --input → tokio runtime → execute → print JSON → exit 0/1
```

